HEADWORD: Taeniata
<hw>Tae`ni*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
L. <ets>taenia</ets> a ribbon.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division
of Ctenophora including those which have a long, ribbonlike body. The
Venus's girdle is the most familiar example.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

